# Study Guide architecture (agents)

## Layers
- **Strategy** = `Study_Guide/` (companies, topics, archetypes, `SUMMARY.md` for GitBook)
- **Library** = root `🎯 Interview Prep Resources.md` + `Interview_Prep_Resources_Context.md`
- **Status SoT** = `Study_Guide/companies/README.md`
- **Feedback** = `FEEDBACK.md` + `.github/ISSUE_TEMPLATE` + Discussions (no Google Form)
- **Living Doc** (often newest library source): see `living-doc-sync.mdc` + `_legacy/README.md`
- Maintainer extracts/plans may live in a **local folder outside git** — never commit them

## Topic file shape (preserve Boss Sheet)
1. Why it matters → 2. Concept summary → 3. Patterns/drills → 4. Question bank  
5. Code sketches → 6. **Boss Sheet (10 · 3 · 5)** → 7. **Resource Panel** (5–15 https links)

## Insert rules
| Change | Where |
|---|---|
| New/deepen company | `companies/_TEMPLATE.md` → tier folder; update status board |
| Deepen topic | Existing `topics/*.md`; wire INDEX/SUMMARY only if **new** file |
| Library PDF/link | Context (± emoji library) + optional one INDEX / Resource Panel row |
| STL day-before | `topics/DSA/STL/` |
| Visitor suggestion | Route per `FEEDBACK.md` |

## Link rules
- Company → topic: relative `../../topics/OS.md`
- Topic → library: absolute `https://…`
- §8 Drive folders = **LC archive (legacy)**, never “OA folder”
- No CTC / LPA / student PII · No monolith Master guide · No invented OA

## Git
- Contributors: branch + PR. Owner (`adityanayak2000`) may push `main`.
- Prefer `git pull --ff-only` before starting. No force-push from agents unless human explicitly orders it.
- One feature per PR/session when possible.

## Extract → merge (when private extracts exist)
1. Read extract INDEX → 2. Paraphrase gaps into topics → 3. Never commit extract files → 4. Keep Boss Sheets
